    "overall_strategy": "The synthesis network for L-Proline is constructed from literature-identified precursors and pathways, focusing on convergent routes from simple feedstocks like formaldehyde, HCN, and ammonia through Strecker-type reactions, HKG cycle intermediates like oxaloacetate, and formaldehyde addition to glycine. Hydrothermal environments produce early reductants and keto acids (e.g., pyruvate, oxaloacetate via Fe\u00b2\u207a catalysis at ~370K), surface environments enable Strecker synthesis and aminonitrile formation in tidal pools with dry-wet cycles (~300-370K, montmorillonite catalysis), and biochemical assembly achieves cyclization and enantioselection in prebiotic pools. Hubs include glycolonitrile, oxaloacetate, and glycine for redundancy. Speculative connections for cyclization are minimized, relying on experimental evidence of proline formation in reduced hydrothermal mixtures and enantioselective amplification; 10 pathways are outlined via sequence variations across environments.",
